div.h1: x86 Privilege Rings: Ring 0 vs. Ring 3
div.p: CPU Protection Model and Current Privilege Level (CPL)
Full Hardware Access All physical memory addressable
All I/O Ports Can access any port (0x00-0xFFFF)
Privileged Instructions CLI, STI, HLT, INVLPG, MOV CRx
Control Registers Can modify CR0, CR2, CR3, CR4
GDT/IDT Management LGDT, LIDT, LLDT, LTR
Page Table Control Read/write any PTE/PDE
I/O Restricted IOPPL check against IOPL
Cannot Modify Control Regs MOV CRx causes #GP
Page Table Read-Only Cannot modify page tables
CPL = CS[1:0] CPU checks CPL on every privileged operation
DPL 0 = Supervisor (kernel only) DPL 3 = User (accessible by all)
Result: CPU pushes error code, jumps to IDT[13] handler
TSS Required: ESP0/SS0 fields tell CPU where kernel stack lives for each process
Via INT instruction or SYSCALL: CPU loads CS from IDT gate (DPL=0) CPU loads SS:ESP from TSS (SS0:ESP0) Handler runs at CPL=0
Via IRET instruction: Pops CS with RPL=3 from stack Pops SS:ESP (user stack pointer) CPL becomes 3
